'''Wilson Isidor''' (born 27 August 2000) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{English football updater|Sunderld}} club [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]. Born in France, he represents the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|477860}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Monaco===
On 11 November 2018, Isidor made his professional debut with Monaco in a 4–0 [[Ligue 1]] loss to [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuille_match/84735/infos|title=LFP.fr – Ligue de Football Professionnel – Ligue 1 Conforama – Saison 2018/2019 – 13ème journée – AS Monaco / Paris Saint-Germain|website=lfp.fr}}</ref> He subsequently had loan spells in [[Championnat National]] with [[Stade Lavallois|Laval]] in the 2019–20 season and [[FC Bastia-Borgo|Bastia-Borgo]] in the 2020–21 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-wilson-isidor-monaco-prete-a-laval/1053826|title=Transferts : Wilson Isidor (Monaco) prêté à Laval|work=L'Équipe|language=fr|date=30 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footamateur.fr/national-lattaquant-monegasque-wilson-isidor-arrive-en-pret-a-bastia-borgo/|title=National. L'attaquant monégasque Wilson Isidor arrive en prêt à Bastia-Borgo|publisher=footamateur.fr|language=fr|date=28 August 2020}}</ref> In his time at Bastia-Borgo he was named Championnat National revelation of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foot-national.com/foot-n1-meilleur-joueur-meilleur-gardien-equipe-type-decouvrez-tous-les-laureats-des-trophees-n1-156227.html|title=N1 : meilleur joueur, meilleur gardien, équipe-type... découvrez tous les lauréats des trophées N1|publisher=foot-national.com|language=fr|date=17 May 2021}}</ref>

===Lokomotiv Moscow===
On 22 January 2022, he signed a 4.5-year contract with Russian club [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Lokomotiv Moscow]]|url=https://www.fclm.ru/ru/publications/news/25508|title=Вилсон Изидор стал игроком "Локомотива"|date=22 January 2022|language=ru}}</ref> He scored at least once in each of his first 6 games in the [[Russian Premier League]], repeating the record for most consecutive games with a goal at the start of the league career that was set a week prior to Isidor's sixth game by [[Yusuf Yazıcı]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Sports.ru|url=https://www.sports.ru/football/1108342503-izidor-zabil-v-5-m-podryad-matche-za-lokomotiv-v-rpl-sochi-s-penalti-o.html|title=Изидор забил в 6-м подряд матче за "Локомотив" в РПЛ и повторил рекорд Языджи|date=17 April 2022|language=ru}}</ref> He was selected player of the month for April 2022 by the Russian Premier League.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Russian Premier League|url=https://premium.premierliga.ru/news-and-media/novosti-i-media_148.html|title=ИЗИДОР, КАРПИН И ЩЕТИНИН – ЛУЧШИЕ В АПРЕЛЕ!|date=29 April 2022|language=ru}}</ref>

On 30 January 2023, [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] announced that Isidor failed their medical test due to persistent knee pain, which cancelled his loan move to the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/wilson-isidor-ne-signera-pas-a-l-olympique-lyonnais |title=Wilson Isidor ne signera pas à l'Olympique Lyonnais |work=Olympique Lyonnais |language=fr |date=30 January 2023 }}</ref>

Upon recovering from injury, Isidor finished the [[2022–23 Russian Premier League]] season with 6 goals in the last 7 games, all after coming in as a second-half substitute.

===Zenit Saint Petersburg===
On 9 September 2023, Isidor moved to [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] on loan for the 2023–24 season. Zenit reported that the contract includes an option to buy, while Lokomotiv reported it as an obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|url=https://fc-zenit.ru/news/2023-09-09-vilson-izidor-prodolzhit-kareru-v-zenite.htm|title=Вильсон Изидор продолжит карьеру в "Зените"|date=9 September 2023|language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Lokomotiv Moscow|url=https://www.fclm.ru/news/n/isidor-zenit-loan/|title=ИЗИДОР ПЕРЕШЁЛ В "ЗЕНИТ" НА ПРАВАХ АРЕНДЫ|date=9 September 2023|language=ru}}</ref> The transfer was officially made permanent on 5 July 2024.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Lokomotiv Moscow|url=https://www.fclm.ru/news/n/zenit-okonchatelno-vykupil-izidora-u-lokomotiva/|title="ЗЕНИТ" ОКОНЧАТЕЛЬНО ВЫКУПИЛ ИЗИДОРА У "ЛОКОМОТИВА"|date=5 July 2024|language=ru}}</ref>

===Sunderland===
On 23 August 2024, Isidor joined [[EFL Championship]] club [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] on an initial season-long loan deal with the option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.safc.com/news/2024/august/23/Isidor-arrives-on-Wearside/|title=Isidor arrives on Wearside|website=safc.com|date=23 August 2024|accessdate=23 August 2024}}</ref>

On 1 February 2025, Isidor signed a permanent deal with Sunderland, with a contract running until the summer of 2028.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.safc.com/news/2025/february/01/wilson-isidor-completes-wearside-move/|title=Isidor completes Wearside move
|website=safc.com|date=1 February 2025|accessdate=1 February 2025}}</ref> On 9 May, Isidor scored in Sunderland's 2–1 away win over [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] in the first leg of their [[2025 English Football League play-offs#Championship|Championship play-off]] semi-final tie.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.efl.com/match-centre/g2554219?|title=Coventry City 1–2 Sundetland|website=EFL|date=9 May 2025|access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref> Sunderland would go on to reach the [[2025 EFL Championship play-off final|play-off final]] against [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]] on 24 May; they scored two late goals in the second half to secure promotion, marking the club's return to the [[Premier League]] since the [[2016–17 Sunderland A.F.C. season|2016–17 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/may/24/sunderland-promoted-to-premier-league-championship-playoff-final-sheffield-united|title=Sunderland snatch promotion to Premier League by beating Sheffield United in playoff final|website=the Guardian|date=25 May 2025|access-date=17 August 2025}}</ref>

On 16 August 2025, Isidor scored Sunderland's third goal in their 3–0 win over [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham]] on the club's return to the [[2025–26 Premier League|Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/sunderland-jarrod-bowen-premier-league-west-ham-stadium-of-light-b2808926.html|title=Sunderland beat West Ham on return to Premier League|website=The Independent|date=16 August 2025|accessdate=17 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Isidor is of Haitian and Malagasy descent.<ref name="haitiantimes"/> He was a youth international for France.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Le-monegasque-wilson-isidor-se-regale-avec-les-u19-francais/949152|title=Le Monégasque Wilson Isidor se régale avec les U19 français|last=Rédaction}}</ref> In March 2026, he committed to representing [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] internationally, and was named in the squad for the friendly matches against [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]] and [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]].<ref name="haitiantimes">{{cite web |url=https://haitiantimes.com/2026/03/19/english-premier-league-star-isidor-commits-to-haiti-after-fan-push-ahead-of-world-cup/ |title=English Premier League star Isidor commits to Haiti after fan push ahead of World Cup |publisher=Haitian Times |date=19 March 2026 }}</ref>

